The paper focuses on using deep learning methods for vehicle detection, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Faster R-CNN and R-CNN, which are both machine learning algorithms, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the evaluation of a trained detector, which suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of experimental results, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
